Applications ->
a. customer evaluation
b. fraud detection


Classification error matrix
a. Confution matrix - a confusion matrix is an nxn matrix used for evaluating the performance of a classification model, where n is the number of target classes.
	-> true positive : actual positive and predicted positive   
	-> false positive : actual negative and predicted positive  {type 1 error}
	-> false negative : actual positive and predicted negative  {type 2 error}
	-> true negative : actual negative and predicted negative

     # Accuracy : TP+TN / TP+FP+TN+FN
     # Recall/Sensitivity/Capture rate : identifying all positive instances {TP/TP+FN} 
     # Precision : identifying only positive instances {TP/TP+FP} 
     # Specificity : avoiding false alarms {TN/FP+TN}
     # F1 Score/ Harmonic mean : 2(P*R/P+R)
   
   
=> bagged decision tree hasve 

